<figureCitation id="39E72A1A075DFFC612B802FDFE4AAE34" box="[390,466,247,273]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="35.[132,143,1962,1979]" captionTargetBox="[133,1455,215,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-28@36.[698,1267,768,1324]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIG. 16. — Stenodactylina insignis (Oppel,1862), Stenodactylina shotoverigiganti n. sp. and Stenodactylina granulifera (Secrétan,1964):A, holotype of S. insignis (Oxfordian, Haute-Saône, France); B, holotype MFN 2236 P1383/2 MB.A.1536 of Eryma anisodactylus Krause,1891 (Kimmeridgian, Holzen,Germany); C, specimen IRSNB without number of S. insignis (Kimmeridgian, La Rochelle, France); D-G, holotype NHMUK 24559 of S. shotoverigiganti n. sp. (Oxfordian, Shotover, United Kingdom):right lateral view (D), left lateral view (E), schema (F), dorsal view (G); H-J, holotype MNHN.F.R03975 of S. granulifera (Kimmeridgian,Antsalova, Madagascar): lateral view (H), schema (J); C, D, holotype MNHN.F.R03974 of Eryma madagascariensis Secrétan, 1964 (Kimmeridgian, Antsalova, Madagascar). Abbreviations:a, branchiocardiac groove;b, antennal groove; b1, hepatic groove; c, postcervical groove; d, gastro-orbital groove; e1e, cervical groove; i, inferior groove;ip, intercalated plate; χ, attachment site of adductor testis muscle;ω, attachment site of mandibular muscle.Photographs:A, L. Cazes;B-E, G,J. Devillez; H, J, C. Lemzaouda. Line drawings: J. Devillez. Scale bars: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4498594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4498594/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
D-G)
</paragraph>
