</taxonomicName>
. Only the ω area is inflated while it is flat in some species (
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075DFFC617B702FDFB65AE34" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1161,1277,247,273]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075DFFC617B702FDFB65AE34" box="[1161,1277,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">S. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075DFFC6163202FDFA30AE34" baseAuthorityName="Moret" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1292,1448,247,273]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075DFFC6163202FDFA30AE34" box="[1292,1448,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">S. delphinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
